From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000007 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: NixOS module overlay <noreply@example.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Point Zotero 7 client at a self-hosted server

The default zotero/zotero (Zotero 7) client is hardcoded to talk to
api.zotero.org / www.zotero.org / stream.zotero.org. To redirect it
to a self-hosted dataserver, edit resource/config.mjs in the
installed app and replace `zotero.example.com` below with your own
hostname (the same value as services.zotero-selfhost.infrastructure.hostname).

Only DOMAIN_NAME, BASE_URI, WWW_BASE_URL, API_URL, and STREAMING_URL
are touched. The other zotero.org subdomains (REPOSITORY_URL,
SERVICES_URL, PROXY_AUTH_URL, FEEDBACK_URL, BOOKMARKLET_URL,
DICTIONARIES_URL, etc) point at upstream Zotero infrastructure that
the self-host doesn't replace — leave them alone unless you want
those features broken.

Note: changing BASE_URI from `http://zotero.org/` to your hostname
breaks dc:relation matching for items synced from upstream
zotero.org. For a pure self-host with no upstream sync, this is
fine. If you're hybrid-syncing, set BASE_URI back to
`http://zotero.org/` to keep relation URIs stable.

This patch is for Zotero 7 (config.mjs ESM module). For older
Zotero 6 see 0001-client-config-for-localhost.patch which targets
the old resource/config.js layout.
---
 resource/config.mjs | 10 +++++-----
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

--- a/resource/config.mjs
+++ b/resource/config.mjs
@@ -2,7 +2,7 @@
 	GUID: 'zotero@zotero.org',
 	ID: 'zotero', // used for db filename, etc.
 	CLIENT_NAME: 'Zotero',
-	DOMAIN_NAME: 'zotero.org',
+	DOMAIN_NAME: 'zotero.example.com',
 	PRODUCER: 'Digital Scholar',
 	PRODUCER_URL: 'https://digitalscholar.org',
 	REPOSITORY_URL: 'https://repo.zotero.org/repo/',
@@ -9,8 +9,8 @@
-	BASE_URI: 'http://zotero.org/',
-	WWW_BASE_URL: 'https://www.zotero.org/',
+	BASE_URI: 'https://zotero.example.com/',
+	WWW_BASE_URL: 'https://zotero.example.com/',
 	PROXY_AUTH_URL: 'https://zoteroproxycheck.s3.amazonaws.com/test',
-	API_URL: 'https://api.zotero.org/',
-	STREAMING_URL: 'wss://stream.zotero.org/',
+	API_URL: 'https://zotero.example.com/',
+	STREAMING_URL: 'wss://zotero.example.com/stream/',
 	SERVICES_URL: 'https://services.zotero.org/',
 	API_VERSION: 3,
 	CONNECTOR_MIN_VERSION: '5.0.39', // show upgrade prompt for requests from below this version
